wifi: mt76: mt7925: fix reported txpower always showing 3 dBm

mt76_get_txpower() computes the reported TX power from
phy->txpower_cur, but the mt7925 driver never assigns this field.
It stays at 0, causing iw to always report 3 dBm regardless of
actual transmit power:

  DIV_ROUND_UP(0 + 6, 2) = 3

The actual RF output is unaffected - firmware receives correct SKU
power tables via set_rate_txpower. Only the value reported to
userspace through iw and nl80211 is wrong.

Fix this by computing the effective TX power for the current
operating channel after programming the per-band SKU tables,
following the same pattern used by mt7996.

Link: https://github.com/jetm/mediatek-mt7927-dkms/issues/47
Reported-by: Loong0x00 <loong0x00@users.noreply.github.com>
Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
Tested-by: Marcin Wróblewski <mawroble@gmail.com>
Tested-by: Clément Metz <metz.clement@gmail.com>

cb234606f197714fd0e282973e2ba41068595d3f
diff --git a/mt7925/mcu.c b/mt7925/mcu.c
index 0755fee..d42025a 100644
--- a/mt7925/mcu.c
+++ b/mt7925/mcu.c
@@ -3839,2 +3839,14 @@ int mt7925_mcu_set_rate_txpower(struct mt76_phy *phy)
 
+	if (phy->chandef.chan) {
+		struct mt76_power_limits la = {};
+		int tx_power;
+
+		tx_power = mt76_get_power_bound(phy,
+						mdev->hw->conf.power_level);
+		tx_power = mt76_get_rate_power_limits(phy,
+						      phy->chandef.chan,
+						      &la, tx_power);
+		phy->txpower_cur = tx_power;
+	}
+
 	return 0;
